		</tr>
	</tbody></table></div>
<p class=3D"center">(Yes, both Quadrant's II and III are "Add 180=C2=B0")</=
p>=20

<div class=3D"example"> <img src=3D"https://www.mathsisfun.com/geometry/ima=
ges/polar-example-1.gif" alt=3D"polar example 1" class=3D"floatRt" height=
=3D"168" width=3D"178">=20
	<h3>Example: P <em>=3D</em> (=E2=88=923, 10)</h3>=20

	<p>P is in <b>Quadrant II</b></p>=20
	<ul>=20
