r>
r <em>=3D</em> =E2=88=9A109 <em>=3D</em> <b>10,4</b> to 1 decimal place</li=
>=20
		<li>=CE=B8 <em>=3D</em> tan<sup>-1</sup>(10/=E2=88=923)<br>
=CE=B8 <em>=3D</em> tan<sup>-1</sup>(=E2=88=923,33...)</li>=20
	</ul>=20
	<p>The calculator value for tan<sup>-1</sup>(=E2=88=923,33...) is =E2=88=
=9273,3=C2=B0</p>=20
	<div class=3D"so"> The rule for Quadrant II is: <span style=3D"font-weight=
: bold;">Add 180=C2=B0 to the calculator value</span></div>
<div class=3D"so">=CE=B8 <em>=3D</em> =E2=88=9273,3=C2=B0 + 180<span style=
=3D"font-weight: bold;">=C2=B0 <em>=3D</em></span> 106,7=C2=B0</div>
